    "(i) If φ ∶ a → b is a BP-map then: (a) κ b = φ(κ a) equivalently φ is a BC-map of (I, κ a) to (J, κ b) (b) σ b = φ(σ a) equivalently φ is a BC-map of (I, σ a) to (J, σ b) (ii) If φ ∶ a → b is an SP-map then: (a) φ(σ a) ⊂ σ b equivalently φ is an SC-map of (I, σ a) to (J, σ b) (b) ∀t ∈ κ b, ∃s ∈ κ a ∶ φ(s) ⊂ tDefinition and Notation 3.1.5 Let φ ∶ I → J be a function.",
